JOHANNESBURG - Action South Africa in KwaZulu-Natal has expressed concern following the shooting of its Newcastle councillor Mzwakhe Mbatha. Mbatha was shot by an unknown gunman on Wednesday night. He sustained a gunshot wound to the face and is currently in hospital. KZN ActionSA spokesperson Busi Radebe said: “At this time, we cannot confirm whether or not the attack was personal or politically motivated. We look forward to the police investigating this matter. We wish councillor Mbatha a speedy recovery.”